(227, '类人组', '', 115, '', '', '', 1, 0, '', '', '', 1491388200, '<p style="box-sizing:border-box;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:12px;color:#333333;font-family:\'Helvetica Neue\', Roboto, sans-serif;font-size:14px;line-height:24px;white-space:normal;">\n	<span style="box-sizing:border-box;color:#666666;font-family:arial, sans-serif;font-size:18px;line-height:21px;text-align:justify;">\n	<h1 class="page-title" style="text-align:center;box-sizing:border-box;font-size:36px;margin:0px;font-family:\'Helvetica Neue\', Roboto, sans-serif;line-height:1;color:#333333;white-space:normal;background-color:#F5F6FA;">\n		RoboCup足球类人组\n	</h1>\n<br />\n<br />\nIn the Humanoid League, autonomous robots with a human-like body plan and human-like senses play soccer against each other. Dynamic walking, running, and kicking the ball while maintaining balance, visual perception of the ball, other players, and the field, self-localization, and team play are among the many research issues investigated in the league.&nbsp;</span><br style="box-sizing:border-box;margin:0px;padding:0px;outline:0px;color:#666666;font-family:arial, sans-serif;font-size:18px;line-height:21px;text-align:justify;" />\n<span style="box-sizing:border-box;color:#666666;font-family:arial, sans-serif;font-size:18px;line-height:21px;text-align:justify;">The league is divided in 3 subleagues, according to robot sizes: Teen Size, Kid Size and Adult Size.</span>\n</p>\n<p style="box-sizing:border-box;margin-top:0px;margin-bottom:12px;color:#333333;font-family:\'Helvetica Neue\', Roboto, sans-serif;font-size:14px;line-height:24px;white-space:normal;">\n	<span style="box-sizing:border-box;color:#666666;font-family:arial, sans-serif;font-size:18px;line-height:21px;text-align:justify;"><a href="http://wiki.robocup.org/wiki/Humanoid_League" target="_blank" style="box-sizing:border-box;color:#D10400;text-decoration:none;margin:0px;padding:0px;outline:0px;cursor:pointer;text-align:left;">Soccer Humanoid League</a></span>\n</p>', '<s